The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, April 1 (PTI): The Delhi consumer commission has directed Spicejet to pay Rs 30,000 as compensation to a passenger for not providing essential facilities after its flight was rescheduled for next day.          
	Himadri Sharma and her parents had boarded the flight from Calcutta on December 31, 2006, but it could not land in Delhi because of bad weather and was sent back to the originating city.                  
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): A special CBI court has postponed its verdict in the alleged rape and murder of eight-year-old Aarti in the Nithari cases after it decided to re-examine an Uttar Pradesh police officer who led the initial probe. The judge asked Dinesh Kumar Yadav to testify on April 15.                   
	 Madurai (PTI): A man has been sentenced to life and his parents to seven years imprisonment after they were found guilty of harassing their daughter-in-law over dowry demands and abetting her suicide. The woman also killed her daughter before committing suicide three years ago.                   
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): An Ahmedabad court on Wednesday extended the police custody of former Gujarat minister Maya Kodanani and former VHP leader Jaideep Patel till April 4. Kodanani and Patel were arrested recently in the 2002 Naroda Patia and Naroda Gram post-Godhra riot case.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A century-old manufacturing unit of Ayurvedic medicine at Panvel in Maharashtra is facing protests from local people because of pollution caused by smoke emitting from its plant. MNS activists alleged that the smoke was hazardous to health.                   
	 Salem (PTI): Four earth movers and one truck allegedly used in illegal mining of magnesite ore at the IT park in Karupur in Salem district were seized on Wednesday. Salem deputy police commissioner John Nickelson said activists protesting illegal mining detained the vehicles.                                                                                                                           
